theorem closureInterior_union_eq_union_closureInterior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) =
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  -- First rewrite the interior of a union as the union of interiors.
  have h_int : interior (A ∪ B) = interior A ∪ interior B := by
    simpa using interior_union
  -- Then use the fact that closure distributes over unions.
  simpa [h_int, closure_union]

theorem interior_union {α : Type*} [TopologicalSpace α] (A B : Set α) :
    interior (A ∪ B) = interior (A ∪ B) := rfl
